===Etymology 1===
From {{etyl|enm|en}} {{m|enm|thank}}, from {{etyl|ang|en}} {{m|ang|þanc||thought, favour, grace, pleasure, satisfaction, thanks}}, from {{etyl|gem-pro|en}} {{m|gem-pro|*þankaz||thought, remembrance, gratitude}}, from {{etyl|ine-pro|en}} {{m|ine-pro|*tong-}}, {{m|ine-pro|*teng-||to think}}. Cognate with {{cog|stq|Tonk}}, {{cog|fy|tank}}, Dutch {{m|nl|dank}}, Low German {{m|nds-de|Dank}}, German {{m|de|Dank}}, Danish {{m|da|tak}}, Swedish {{m|sv|tack}}, Faroese {{m|fo|tøkk}}, Icelandic {{m|is|þökk}}. Related to [[thought]].

====Noun====
{{en-noun}}

# {{lb|en|obsolete}} An expression of appreciation; a thought.
